"method"
"decodeFields"
"columnarEngine::decodeFields"
"adapters/dalgo2memory/columnar.go"
"go"
581
615
0
1
"decodeFields converts a record's data (a struct, pointer, or map[string]any)\ninto one reflect.Value per column, typed to the column's element type.\n\nThe record is first marshaled (rejecting non-serializable values) and\nunmarshaled into a normalized map, matching the Serialized engine's\nvalidation and reassembly view; an unknown field is rejected there. Scalar\ncolumns are then decoded from the normalized value. A reference-bearing\ncolumn is deep-copied via the round-trip when the collection is faithful;\nwhen the opt-out is set and the source is a live struct, the caller's field\nvalue is stored by direct reflection copy (sharing references). Fields absent\nfrom the data decode to the column's zero value."
"(data any) ([]reflect.Value, error)"
